Annotation.note:
Compute the intersection points of four unit circles with centers at
$(0,0), (1,0), (-1,0)$ and $(0,1)$ as the singular locus of the
product of their defining equations. Note that the origin has
multiplicity greater than 1.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple 
 p:=(x^2+y^2-1)*((x-1)^2+y^2-1)*((x+1)^2+y^2-1)*(x^2+(y-1)^2-1);
 polys:=map(expand,[p,diff(p,x),diff(p,y)]);
 vars:=[x,y];
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
Singular Locus
\end{keywords}

First discussed in [BIB/Buchberger_87a]
